A novel method for the automated and customized analysis of bias triangles in quantum dot (QD) devicesis introduced to understand spin physics. Due to challenges in data quality and availability as well as the subtlety of physical phenomena of interest, human labeling and verification are necessary. This approach circumvents the need for human input or large training datasets to inform supervised learning approaches, while also enabling the automation of pixelwise shape and feature labeling. In particular, we demonstrate that pauli spin blockade (PSB) detection can be conducted effectively, efficiently, and without any training data as a direct result of this approach.
